description:
Summary: 
Sword is on a mission to free two billion people from pain through AI Care. The Computer Vision Trainee will be involved in designing and evaluating model training experiments, contributing to data analysis, and enhancing the quality of the team’s output in a fast-paced environment.

Responsibilities: 
Design and evaluate model training experiments for human pose estimation problems;
Experiment training with different human pose estimation model architectures;
Perform dataset analysis (look for useful insights, possible biases, etc.);
Contribute to the quality of the team’s output by developing and executing test plans and creating internal tools and scripts for automation and testing;
Troubleshoot, debug and maintain documentation.

Qualification: 
Required
  -Master’s degree in Engineering, Computer Science, Physics or Mathematics;
  -Ability to solve complex problems with software;
  -Solid knowledge of Python;
  -Good technical foundation in Machine Learning (models training, understanding concepts like dataset augmentation, loss functions, back propagation, optimizers, etc) but above all ability to learn about new technical topics;
  -Ability to visualize and interpret data of different types;
  -Critical thinking, self-direction, results-oriented mindset;
  -Ability to collaborate effectively with technical and non-technical stakeholders and within the team;
  -Passion to work in fast paced working environments.

Preferred
  -Experience in Computer Vision related topics.
